The paper deals with frequency estimation and line spectral estimation, which are topics related to signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves numerical methods and optimization, which suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as another possible sub-category. The use of semidefinite programming and atomic norm methods indicates cs.SD (Systems and Control) as a potential sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a new result related to the positive real lemma for trigonometric polynomials, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category.
